      "id": 1,
      "text": "Machias village was originally called Machias Five Corners or Chickasaw and in the 1890s housed three churches, a school, a hotel, four stores, and a cheese factory.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
