      ],
      "source": "https://historicpath.com/history/machias"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The town’s name comes from Machias, Maine, where the first settlers arrived from in 1807.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        27
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.machiasny.gov/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Major Timothy Butler first settled along Ischua Creek in 1807, tapping 1,400 maple trees that later fueled the town’s maple sugar industry.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        16,
        18
